---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How FraiseQL Works - Database-First Compilation Pipeline"
  description="Deep dive into FraiseQL's 3-stage compilation pipeline: authoring, compilation, and runtime execution."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>How FraiseQL Works</h1>
    <p>
      FraiseQL transforms database-first schema into compiled GraphQL execution
      plans.
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Stage 1: Authoring</h2>
      <p>
        Write your schema in Python or TypeScript using database-centric
        decorators. FraiseQL generates schema.json with type definitions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Stage 2: Compilation</h2>
      <p>
        The Rust compiler validates and optimizes your schema, generating
        schema.compiled.json with precomputed SQL execution plans.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Stage 3: Runtime</h2>
      <p>
        Pure Rust server loads the compiled schema and executes queries with
        deterministic paths—no runtime interpretation, no N+1 queries.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p>
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
